---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { SITE_URL } from "../constants";
---

<Layout
  title="ringfence: sandbox npm install from supply-chain worms"
  description="Sandbox npm, pnpm, yarn, and bun installs with bwrap. Keep SSH keys, cloud credentials, and .env files hidden from malicious postinstall scripts. No config."
>
  <div class="stripe-bg min-h-screen">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header
      class="border-b border-border"
    >
      <nav class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl items-center justify-between px-6 py-5">
        <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span
            class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent text-sm font-bold text-base"
          >
            S
          </span>
          <span class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-body">ringfence</span>
        </a>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/asmyshlyaev177/ringfence"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-body transition hover:border-border-strong hover:bg-elevated"
          >
            <svg class="h-4 w-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path
                d="M12 0C5.37 0 0 5.37 0 12c0 5.31 3.435 9.795 8.205 11.385.6.105.825-.255.825-.57 0-.285-.015-1.23-.015-2.235-3.015.555-3.795-.735-4.035-1.41-.135-.345-.72-1.41-1.23-1.695-.42-.225-1.02-.78-.015-.795.945-.015 1.62.87 1.845 1.23 1.08 1.815 2.805 1.305 3.495.99.105-.78.42-1.305.765-1.605-2.67-.3-5.46-1.335-5.46-5.925 0-1.305.465-2.385 1.23-3.225-.12-.3-.54-1.53.12-3.18 0 0 1.005-.315 3.3 1.23.96-.27 1.98-.405 3-.405s2.04.135 3 .405c2.295-1.56 3.3-1.23 3.3-1.23.66 1.65.24 2.88.12 3.18.765.84 1.23 1.905 1.23 3.225 0 4.605-2.805 5.625-5.475 5.925.435.375.81 1.095.81 2.22 0 1.605-.015 2.895-.015 3.3 0 .315.225.69.825.57A12.02 12.02 0 0024 12c0-6.63-5.37-12-12-12z"
              />
            </svg>
            GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <!-- Hero -->
      <section
        class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-border"
      >
        <div
          class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 hero-glow"
        />
        <div
          class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pt-28 pb-24 text-center"
        >
          <div class="mb-8 flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
            <span class="badge badge-warning">Beta</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-muted">v0.1.0 &middot; Linux &amp; macOS</span>
          </div>

          <h1
            class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-5xl font-extrabold leading-[1.08] tracking-tight sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl"
          >
            Install packages.
            <br />
            <span class="text-accent">Not threats.</span>
          </h1>

          <p
            class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted"
          >
            ringfence runs <code class="rounded bg-elevated px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm text-body">npm install</code>,
            <code class="rounded bg-elevated px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm text-body">pnpm add</code>, and friends
            inside a lightweight
            <strong class="text-body">bwrap sandbox</strong>. Your SSH keys, cloud credentials, and
            <code class="rounded bg-elevated px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm text-body">.env</code> files stay yours. No
            allowlists. No daemon. No config.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-10 flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
            <a
              href="#install"
              class="glow-ring inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-accent px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-bold text-base uppercase tracking-wider transition hover:bg-accent-hover"
            >
              Get started
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" />
              </svg>
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://github.com/asmyshlyaev177/ringfence#readme"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold text-body transition hover:border-border-strong hover:bg-elevated"
            >
              Read the docs
            </a>
          </div>

          <div
            class="mt-14 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-border bg-surface/50 px-5 py-2"
          >
            <span class="flex h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-success"></span>
            <span class="text-xs text-muted">No <code class="font-mono text-xs text-body">sudo</code> required &middot; Local dev dependency &middot; Open source (MIT)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Problem: The supply-chain threat -->
      <section class="border-b border-border">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
          <div
            class="relative rounded-2xl border border-danger-border bg-danger-subtle p-8 md:p-12"
          >
<div
          class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 hero-glow"
        />
            <div class="relative">
              <span class="badge badge-danger mb-4">Live threat</span>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-danger md:text-4xl">
                The TanStack supply-chain worm
              </h2>
              <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
                In May 2026, a worm compromised 84 npm packages with valid SLSA Build Level 3 provenance.
                Postinstall scripts exfiltrated CI/CD secrets, SSH keys, cloud credentials, and crypto wallets.
                It spread undetected because it looked legitimate.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
                ringfence stops this class of attack at the OS level. Postinstall scripts run in a sandbox where
                your secrets simply do not exist.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- How it works -->
      <section class="border-b border-border" id="how-it-works">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
          <div class="text-center">
            <span class="badge badge-sandbox mb-4">How it works</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">
              Three layers of protection
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-muted">
              From shell shim to kernel sandbox, nothing changes in your workflow.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="mt-16 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3"
          >
            <!-- Step 1 -->
            <div class="terminal-card relative flex flex-col">
              <span
                class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent-subtle font-mono text-lg font-bold text-accent"
              >
                01
              </span>
              <h3 class="mt-5 text-lg font-bold">Global shims</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
                The one-line installer puts lightweight shims on your PATH. No aliases, no wrappers to remember.
                When you run <code class="font-mono text-xs">npm install</code>, ringfence intercepts it automatically.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Arrow connector (desktop) -->
            <div class="hidden items-center justify-center md:flex">
              <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-border-strong" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
              </svg>
            </div>

            <!-- Step 2 -->
            <div class="terminal-card relative flex flex-col">
              <span
                class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent-subtle font-mono text-lg font-bold text-accent"
              >
                02
              </span>
              <h3 class="mt-5 text-lg font-bold">bwrap sandbox</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
                The install runs inside a Bubblewrap container. Secrets in
                <code class="font-mono text-xs">~/.ssh</code>, <code class="font-mono text-xs">~/.aws</code>,
                and your environment variables are invisible to postinstall scripts.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Arrow connector (desktop) -->
            <div class="hidden items-center justify-center md:flex">
              <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-border-strong" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="right" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
              </svg>
            </div>

            <!-- Step 3 -->
            <div class="terminal-card relative flex flex-col">
              <span
                class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent-subtle font-mono text-lg font-bold text-accent"
              >
                03
              </span>
              <h3 class="mt-5 text-lg font-bold">Zero config</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 flex-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted">
                Non-install commands pass through unchanged. No allowlists, no policy files, no daemon.
                Just sandboxed package management that works out of the box.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Package managers -->
      <section class="border-b border-border">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
          <div class="text-center">
            <span class="badge badge-sandbox mb-4">Compatible</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">
              Works with every major package manager
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-muted">
              Your existing commands. Same flags. Same output. Just sandboxed.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-12 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="terminal-card">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span
                  class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-elevated font-mono text-sm font-bold text-accent"
                >
                  n
                </span>
                <span class="font-bold">npm</span>
              </div>
              <pre
                class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg bg-base p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed"
              ><code class="font-mono text-success">$ <span class="text-body">npm install</span> express</code></pre>
            </div>

            <div class="terminal-card">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span
                  class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-elevated font-mono text-sm font-bold text-sandbox"
                >
                  p
                </span>
                <span class="font-bold">pnpm</span>
              </div>
              <pre
                class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg bg-base p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed"
              ><code class="font-mono text-success">$ <span class="text-body">pnpm add</span> zod</code></pre>
            </div>

            <div class="terminal-card">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span
                  class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-elevated font-mono text-sm font-bold text-sandbox"
                >
                  y
                </span>
                <span class="font-bold">yarn</span>
              </div>
              <pre
                class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg bg-base p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed"
              ><code class="font-mono text-success">$ <span class="text-body">yarn add</span> react</code></pre>
            </div>

            <div class="terminal-card">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span
                  class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-elevated font-mono text-sm font-bold text-accent"
                >
                  b
                </span>
                <span class="font-bold">bun</span>
              </div>
              <pre
                class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg bg-base p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed"
              ><code class="font-mono text-success">$ <span class="text-body">bun add</span> @hono/hono</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Install -->
      <section class="border-b border-border" id="install">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
          <div class="text-center">
            <span class="badge badge-warning mb-4">Install</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">
              Two commands. Any project.
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-muted">
              Install as a dev dependency, then activate. Works with npm, pnpm, yarn, and bun.
            </p>
          </div>

<div class="terminal-card relative mx-auto mt-10 max-w-2xl">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between border-b border-border pb-3">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="flex h-3 w-3 rounded-full border border-danger/40"></span>
                <span class="flex h-3 w-3 rounded-full border border-accent/40"></span>
                <span class="flex h-3 w-3 rounded-full border border-sandbox/40"></span>
                <span class="ml-2 text-xs text-muted">terminal</span>
              </div>
              <button
                id="copy-btn"
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 rounded-md border border-border bg-elevated px-2.5 py-1 text-xs text-muted transition hover:text-body hover:border-border-strong"
                onclick="var b=this; navigator.clipboard.writeText('npm i -D ringfence'+String.fromCharCode(10)+'npx ringfence'); var s=document.getElementById('copy-status'); b.querySelector('span').textContent='Copied!'; s.textContent='Copied!'; setTimeout(function(){b.querySelector('span').textContent='Copy'; s.textContent=''}, 1500)"
                aria-label="Copy install command"
                type="button"
              >
                <svg class="h-3.5 w-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.75 17.25v3.375c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-9.75a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V7.875c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125H6.75a9.06 9.06 0 011.5.124m7.5 10.376h3.375c.621 0 1.125-.504 1.125-1.125V11.25c0-4.46-3.243-8.161-7.5-8.876a9.06 9.06 0 00-1.5-.124H9.375c-.621 0-1.125.504-1.125 1.125v3.5m7.5 10.375H9.375a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125v-9.25m12 6.625v-1.875a3.375 3.375 0 00-3.375-3.375h-1.5a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125v-1.5a3.375 3.375 0 00-3.375-3.375H9.75" />
                </svg>
                <span>Copy</span>
              </button>
            </div>
            <span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite" id="copy-status"></span>
            <pre
              class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto"
            ><code class="font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed"><span class="text-success">$</span> <span class="text-body">npm i -D ringfence</span>
<span class="text-success">$</span> <span class="text-body">npx ringfence</span></code></pre>
          </div>

          <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-xl text-center text-sm text-dim">
            Auto-detects your OS and sets up
            <code class="rounded bg-surface px-1 font-mono text-xs text-body">bubblewrap</code> (Linux)
            or <code class="rounded bg-surface px-1 font-mono text-xs text-body">Docker</code> (macOS).
            Then every <code class="rounded bg-surface px-1 font-mono text-xs text-body">npm install</code> runs sandboxed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- What's protected -->
      <section class="border-b border-border">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
          <div class="text-center">
            <span class="badge badge-danger mb-4">Protected</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">
              What ringfence hides
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-muted">
              Every install runs in a clean room. These never reach postinstall scripts.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-12 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
            <div class="terminal-card">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-lg">&#128274;</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">Credentials</span>
              </div>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm text-muted">
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">.env, .env.*</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">.netrc, .pgpass</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">credentials, secrets</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="terminal-card">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-lg">&#128481;</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">SSH &amp; TLS keys</span>
              </div>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm text-muted">
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">id_rsa*, id_ed25519*</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">*.pem, *.key, *.crt</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">known_hosts</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="terminal-card">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-lg">&#9729;</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">Cloud config</span>
              </div>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm text-muted">
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">~/.aws, ~/.azure</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">service-account*.json</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">gcloud-*.json</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="terminal-card">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-lg">&#9881;</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">Environment vars</span>
              </div>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm text-muted">
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">*TOKEN*, *SECRET*</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">*API_KEY*, *PASSWORD*</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">AWS_, GITHUB_, NPM_</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="terminal-card">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-lg">&#128196;</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">Certificates</span>
              </div>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm text-muted">
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">*.pfx, *.p12, *.jks</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">*.gpg, *.asc</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">*.cer, *.keystore</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="terminal-card">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-lg">&#128737;</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">Entire $HOME</span>
              </div>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm text-muted">
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">Replaced with tmpfs</li>
                <li class="font-mono text-xs">~/.ssh, ~/.gnupg hidden</li>
                <li class="text-xs text-muted">
                  <em>Except ~/.npmrc, ~/.yarnrc</em>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-10 text-center text-sm text-dim">
            <code class="rounded bg-surface px-1 font-mono text-xs text-body">~/.npmrc</code> and
            <code class="rounded bg-surface px-1 font-mono text-xs text-body">~/.yarnrc</code> are mounted
            read-only so private registry auth still works. Everything else in
            <code class="rounded bg-surface px-1 font-mono text-xs text-body">$HOME</code> is invisible.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Footer -->
      <footer class="px-6 py-10">
        <div
          class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl flex-col items-center justify-between gap-4 text-center sm:flex-row"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-dim">
            ringfence &middot; MIT license
          </p>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-6 text-sm text-dim">
            <a
              href="https://github.com/asmyshlyaev177/ringfence"
              class="transition hover:text-body"
            >
              GitHub
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://github.com/asmyshlyaev177/ringfence/issues"
              class="transition hover:text-body"
            >
              Issues
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://github.com/asmyshlyaev177/ringfence?tab=readme-ov-file#contributing"
              class="transition hover:text-body"
            >
              Contribute
            </a>
<span class="text-dim/50">|</span>
           <a
             href="https://asmyshlyaev177.dev"
             class="transition hover:text-body"
           >
             by Alexander Smyshlyaev
           </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>
